      Subinterfaces of IStatus in common.message.status

      interface  IStatusProcessingError
      This is the well-known status error message that is sent when something goes wrong during processing of a message by a visitor - maybe a null pointer exception, divide by 0, etc.

      This is the well-known status error message that is sent when a request message is received asking for a well-known message type.

      This is the well-known status error message that is sent when a Remote Exception occurs while trying to send data to an IMember.
